gaffer.data.element.function

Class ElementAggregator

  • java.lang.Object
    • gaffer.function.processor.Processor<R,PassThroughFunctionContext<R,AggregateFunction>>
      • gaffer.function.processor.Aggregator<String>
        • gaffer.data.element.function.ElementAggregator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class ElementAggregator
extends Aggregator<String>
    Element Aggregator - for aggregating Elements. When Elements are aggregated it is only the Element Properties that are aggregated. Aggregation requires elements to have the same identifiers and group.

    Use ElementAggregator.Builder to build an ElementAggregator.

    To use this aggregator:

    • Use ElementAggregator.Builder to build an ElementAggregator
    • first group Elements with the same identifiers and group together
    • call initFunctions()
    • for each element in the group call aggregate(element)
    • create a new element then call state(newElement) to populate the new element with the aggregated properties
    See Also:
    ElementAggregator.Builder, Aggregator
